import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='yield', data=data)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    ax.axvline(data['yield'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['yield'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average yield of barley across all sites?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='yield', hue='site', multiple='stack', kde=True, element='step', alpha=0.5)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of yield at each site?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
